57#include <openssl/asn1.h>
58#include <openssl/err.h>
59#include <openssl/mem.h>
60#include <openssl/obj.h>
61#include <openssl/x509.h>
62#include <openssl/x509v3.h>
63
64#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_FP_API
65int X509_CRL_print_fp(FILE *fp, X509_CRL *x)
66{
67 BIO *b = BIO_new_fp(fp, BIO_NOCLOSE);
68 if (b == NULL) {
69 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_BUF_LIB);
70 return 0;
71 }
72 int ret = X509_CRL_print(b, x);
73 BIO_free(b);
74 return ret;
75}
76#endif
77
78int X509_CRL_print(BIO *out, X509_CRL *x)
79{
80 STACK_OF(X509_REVOKED) *rev;
81 X509_REVOKED *r;
82 long l;
83 size_t i;
84 char *p;
85
86 BIO_printf(out, "Certificate Revocation List (CRL):\n");
87 l = X509_CRL_get_version(x);
88 BIO_printf(out, "%8sVersion %lu (0x%lx)\n", "", l + 1, l);
89 X509_signature_print(out, x->sig_alg, NULL);
90 p = X509_NAME_oneline(X509_CRL_get_issuer(x), NULL, 0);
91 BIO_printf(out, "%8sIssuer: %s\n", "", p);
92 OPENSSL_free(p);
93 BIO_printf(out, "%8sLast Update: ", "");
94 ASN1_TIME_print(out, X509_CRL_get0_lastUpdate(x));
95 BIO_printf(out, "\n%8sNext Update: ", "");
96 if (X509_CRL_get0_nextUpdate(x))
97 ASN1_TIME_print(out, X509_CRL_get0_nextUpdate(x));
98 else
99 BIO_printf(out, "NONE");
100 BIO_printf(out, "\n");
101
102 X509V3_extensions_print(out, "CRL extensions", x->crl->extensions, 0, 8);
103
104 rev = X509_CRL_get_REVOKED(x);
105
106 if (sk_X509_REVOKED_num(rev) > 0)
107 BIO_printf(out, "Revoked Certificates:\n");
108 else
109 BIO_printf(out, "No Revoked Certificates.\n");
110
111 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_REVOKED_num(rev); i++) {
112 r = sk_X509_REVOKED_value(rev, i);
113 BIO_printf(out, " Serial Number: ");
114 i2a_ASN1_INTEGER(out, r->serialNumber);
115 BIO_printf(out, "\n Revocation Date: ");
116 ASN1_TIME_print(out, r->revocationDate);
117 BIO_printf(out, "\n");
118 X509V3_extensions_print(out, "CRL entry extensions",
119 r->extensions, 0, 8);
120 }
121 X509_signature_print(out, x->sig_alg, x->signature);
122
123 return 1;
124
125}
